{% # Exploration canvas v1.1.0 %}

{% doc %}
  @description
  Shared render scaffold for every exploration section. Renders utility chrome (breadcrumb + intro) as a sibling of the validation content; the validation content is `{{ contents }}` emitted directly under `<theme-section>` with no exploration-imposed wrapper. This keeps validation blocks production-native — they inherit only theme-section's `--content-width` cap + `--gutter` padding, exactly like a real section's children.

  Utility chrome carries its own width discipline (`.exploration__intro` with max-inline-size + padding). It does NOT cascade onto sibling validation content.

  @param {section} section - The section object (passed explicitly because snippets run in isolated scope)
  @param {string} contents - Pre-rendered child blocks markup. Sections capture `{% content_for 'blocks' %}` before rendering this snippet (snippets can't host `content_for`).

  Variables emitted (scoped to section's #base_selector): - `--content-width`: 80rem — overrides production default
  (125rem) so the section is production-like but narrower for visibility - `--block-rhythm-mobile` /
  `--block-rhythm-desktop`: 1rem / 1.5rem — production sections set these via the `spacing` metaobject; exploration uses
  reasonable defaults so blocks have inter-block spacing via the theme-section block-rhythm cascade -
  `--exploration-bleed-extension`: distance a bleeding child shifts to reach the bleed boundary (capped at 125rem
  content cap). Computed as `section_gutter_to_cap + section_padding_inline`. Used by exploration block stylesheets.

  Formula: `max(0px, (min(100dvw, 125rem) - var(--content-width, 125rem)) / 2) + var(--gutter)`. First term = section gutter (capped at 125rem so bleeds don't exceed content cap on wide viewports). Second term = theme-section's padding-inline (responsive: 1.5rem mobile, 3.5rem desktop). Total = full distance from theme-section content edge to bleed boundary. Generalized to whatever `--content-width` resolves to on the section — works at 80rem override or the 125rem production default.

  Temporary scaffold — see BACKLOG.md § Active exploration.

  @example {% render 'exploration--canvas', section: section, contents: contents %}
{% enddoc %}

{% liquid
  assign base_selector = 'shopify-section-' | append: section.id
%}

<theme-section data-modifiers="theme-root">
  {% render 'exploration--breadcrumb' %}

  <header class='exploration__intro'>
    <h1>{{ section.settings.title }}</h1>
    <p>{{ section.settings.description }}</p>
  </header>

  {{ contents }}
</theme-section>

{% capture dynamic_style %}
  --block-rhythm-mobile: 1rem;
  --block-rhythm-desktop: 1.5rem;
  --exploration-bleed-extension: calc(max(0px, (min(100dvw, 125rem) - var(--content-width, 125rem)) / 2) + var(--gutter));
{% endcapture %}
{% render 'utility--dynamic-style', base_selector: base_selector, css_content: dynamic_style %}
